.TH "waybar-systemd-failed-units" "5" "2026-03-23"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
waybar - systemd failed units monitor module
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBsystemd-failed-units\fR module displays the number of failed systemd units.\&
.PP
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
Addressed by \fBsystemd-failed-units\fR
.PP
\fBformat\fR: 
.br
typeof: string  
.br
default: \fB{nr_failed} failed\fR 
.br
The format, how information should be displayed.\& This format is used when other formats aren'\&t specified.\&
.PP
\fBformat-ok\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
This format is used when there are no failing units.\&
.PP
\fBuser\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: \fBtrue\fR 
.br
Option to count user systemd units.\&
.PP
\fBsystem\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: \fBtrue\fR 
.br
Option to count systemwide (PID=1) systemd units.\&
.PP
\fBhide-on-ok\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: \fBtrue\fR 
.br
Option to hide this module when there are no failed units.\&
.PP
\fBtooltip-format\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
default: \fBSystem: {system_state}nUser: {user_state}nFailed units ({nr_failed}):n{failed_units_list}\fR 
.br
Tooltip format shown when there are failed units.\&
.PP
\fBtooltip-format-ok\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
default: \fBSystem: {system_state}nUser: {user_state}\fR 
.br
Tooltip format used when there are no failed units.\&
.PP
\fBtooltip-unit-format\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
default: \fB{name}: {description}\fR 
.br
Format used to render each failed unit inside the tooltip.\& Each item is prefixed with a bullet.\&
.PP
\fBmenu\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
Action that pops up the menu.\&
.PP
\fBmenu-file\fR: 
.br
typeof: string 
.br
Location of the menu descriptor file.\& There needs to be an element of type
.RS 4
GtkMenu with id \fBmenu\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBmenu-actions\fR: 
.br
typeof: array 
.br
The actions corresponding to the buttons of the menu.\&
.PP
\fBexpand\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: false 
.br
Enables this module to consume all leftover space dynamically.\&
.PP
.SH FORMAT REPLACEMENTS
.PP
\fB{nr_failed_system}\fR: Number of failed units from systemwide (PID=1) systemd.\&
.PP
\fB{nr_failed_user}\fR: Number of failed units from user systemd.\&
.PP
\fB{nr_failed}\fR: Number of total failed units.\&
.PP
\fB{system_state}:\fR State of the systemd system session.\&
.PP
\fB{user_state}:\fR State of the systemd user session.\&
.PP
\fB{overall_state}:\fR Overall state of the systemd and user session.\& ("ok" or "degraded")
.PP
\fB{failed_units_list}:\fR Bulleted list of failed units using \fBtooltip-unit-format\fR.\& Empty when
there are no failed units.\&
.PP
The \fBtooltip-unit-format\fR string supports the following replacements:
.PP
\fB{name}\fR: Unit name 
.br
\fB{description}\fR: Unit description 
.br
\fB{load_state}\fR: Unit load state 
.br
\fB{active_state}\fR: Unit active state 
.br
\fB{sub_state}\fR: Unit sub state 
.br
\fB{scope}\fR: Either \fBsystem\fR or \fBuser\fR depending on where the unit originated
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
"systemd-failed-units": {
	"hide-on-ok": false,
	"format": "✗ {nr_failed}",
	"format-ok": "✓",
	"system": true,
	"user": false,
	"tooltip-format": "{nr_failed} failed units:n{failed_units_list}",
	"tooltip-unit-format": "{scope}: {name} ({active_state})",
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
